‘𝐒𝐚𝐯𝐞’ for your Valentine! Valentine’s Day is next week - use this easy template to make something sweet for your Valentine💘 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
𝐃𝐨 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐡𝐚𝐯𝐞 𝐚𝐧𝐲 𝐟𝐮𝐧 𝐕𝐚𝐥𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐞’𝐬 𝐃𝐚𝐲 𝐩𝐥𝐚𝐧𝐬 𝐨𝐫 𝐆𝐚𝐥𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐞’𝐬 𝐃𝐚𝐲 𝐩𝐥𝐚𝐧𝐬? Share in the comments for inspiration!! 💞⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Make a VDay Reel by adding 4 clips of your memories together! ⁣⁣
1️⃣- 2.0 seconds⁣⁣
2️⃣- 2.4 seconds ⁣⁣
3️⃣- 1.5 seconds ⁣⁣
4️⃣- 2.0 seconds ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Here’s what I recommend:⁣⁣
🎥 Go through your camera roll and look for the following clips or photos…⁣⁣
1st - Memorable moment (Proposal, wedding, anniversary, etc.) ⁣⁣
2nd - Evening or sunset spent together ⁣⁣
3rd - You and your Valentine⁣⁣
4th - You two dancing! ⁣⁣
Or just four of your favorite clips or photos together! They don’t have to relate to the lyrics if you don’t have specific clips💕⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Save the four to a new folder (or favorite them) to make them easier to find when putting them in the template💌 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Hit the “Use Template” button while viewing this in full screen mode (tap into it if you are viewing it on your home feed). You’ll have the option to add 4 clips. You can also make it an editing app like InShot! 📱 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Here’s where our clips were shot:⁣⁣
1️⃣ Chapmans Peak 🇿🇦 ⁣⁣
2️⃣ Kruger National Park 🇿🇦 ⁣⁣
3️⃣ Clifton Beach, Cape Town 🇿🇦 ⁣⁣
4️⃣ Glacier National Park, Montana 🇺🇸 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Tag me if you end up using the template so I can hype your video! 💌 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⁣📸 @thewanderingqueen⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣

How to better connect with your partner👇⁣
⁣
Plan adventures together - this gives you something to look forward to 🗓️ ⁣
⁣
An adventure doesn’t have to be an expensive international holiday (although those are fun too!) ✈️ ⁣
⁣
𝐇𝐞𝐫𝐞 𝐚𝐫𝐞 𝐚𝐝𝐯𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐞 𝐢𝐝𝐞𝐚𝐬 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐢𝐧𝐬𝐩𝐢𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧: ⁣
🏡 Local or distant cabin stay (highly recommend @thehighlandermt)⁣
🍱 Eat at a new restaurant with international cuisine (we recently tried an Ethiopian restaurant & loved it) ⁣
🏔️ Go on a new hike (bonus points for a sunset hike - days are getting longer!)⁣
🧺 Stroll through a new park & pack a picnic ⁣
🧖‍♀️ Get a couples massage or spa treatment⁣
🛼 Try a new activity together (rock climbing, roller skating, horse back riding, zip lining, line dancing, pottery, the opportunities are endless)⁣
⁣
Now when you’re on your next adventure (road trip, hike, dinner date, cabin stay, etc.) - 𝐚𝐬𝐤 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐬𝐞 𝐪𝐮𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧𝐬 𝐭𝐨 𝐬𝐩𝐚𝐫𝐤 𝐜𝐨𝐧𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐬𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐝𝐞𝐞𝐩𝐞𝐧 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐫𝐞𝐥𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧𝐬𝐡𝐢𝐩:⁣
⁣
❓What’s a memory from your childhood you would want to relive?⁣
❓If you could pick any decade to grow up in, what would it be?⁣
❓What is your favorite gift you’ve ever received?⁣
❓If you could pick the ideal day to be born, when would it be? Do you like your birthday? Why or why not?⁣
❓What’s your dream way to celebrate your birthday? Imagine money is not a factor. ⁣
❓What’s something that you think people misunderstand about you?⁣
❓If you could be internationally known for one thing, what would it be?⁣
⁣
These all should be followed up with “and why?” ⁣
⁣
When we stayed at @thehighlandermt they had the game “Let’s Get Deep” for couples that had question cards, which we enjoyed to spark new conversations! ⁣
⁣
What’s your favorite adventure to take with your partner? ❤️⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣

Sneak peak of our dreamy engagement shoot in Virgin Islands National Park 🏝️💛⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Thanks to Max of @lindsandmaxphotounderwater for bringing our visions to life & totally exceeding expectations 🥹⁣⁣
⁣⁣
38 photos in a sneak peak album 🤯 here are 10 of our favorites! Check out even more in my stories (a lot are landscape so you’ll get more context of the beautiful scenery). Our minds are blown and we are obsessed!😍⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Which ones are your favorites?🤍⁣⁣
⁣⁣
It was the first time @keithwebberphoto and I did a full shoot in front of the camera together (Keith is typically behind it  or we infrequently set up a tripod to capture us both) 📸 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
We had so much fun & quickly found out trying to get underwater shots is much more difficult than it looks (staying underwater, not blowing out too many bubbles, attempting to tame hair flying everywhere, avoiding drowning) 🤪💦 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
We were humbled between mouthfuls of sea water, alternating between coughing & laughing at the realization we could’ve just done a beach sunset shoot but, never one for “normal,” of course I had to suggest we do something a little more “extreme.” 𝘓𝘦𝘵’𝘴 𝘴𝘩𝘰𝘰𝘵 𝘰𝘶𝘳 𝘦𝘯𝘨𝘢𝘨𝘦𝘮𝘦𝘯𝘵 𝘱𝘩𝘰𝘵𝘰𝘴 𝘶𝘯𝘥𝘦𝘳𝘸𝘢𝘵𝘦𝘳 𝘸𝘩𝘪𝘭𝘦 𝘯𝘦𝘪𝘵𝘩𝘦𝘳 𝘰𝘧 𝘢𝘳𝘦 𝘨𝘳𝘦𝘢𝘵 𝘶𝘯𝘥𝘦𝘳𝘸𝘢𝘵𝘦𝘳 𝘰𝘳 𝘩𝘢𝘷𝘦 𝘢𝘯𝘺 𝘦𝘹𝘱𝘦𝘳𝘪𝘦𝘯𝘤𝘦 𝘸𝘪𝘵𝘩 𝘵𝘩𝘪𝘴 🤪😅😂 Keith is always down for my antics and such a great sport, one of the many reasons I love him so much! 🥹🥰⁣⁣
⁣⁣
This was the first time I opened my eyes underwater without goggles (I used to wear contacts but got lasik surgery a few years ago so now I’m able to) but hadn’t tried until this shoot lol 👀 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I’m always trying to push us out of our comfort zones (because that’s where the magic happens!), and this was no exception ✨ ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
We were rewarded with the most beautiful sunset under a sliver of a crescent moon (my favorite!). Swipe to the last photo to see! The sky celebrated our shoot, burning a firey orange as we packed up our things 🌙 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Also shoutout to my IG friend @bycarlavianna for inspo from her gorgeous engagement shoot in Rio 💕⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣

location.city_name: Exit Glacier, Kenai Fjords National Park

social_posts.post_text:
The first time I did this hike, I was driving back to my cabin in Kenai from a fishing trip in Seward with some family friends and decided to make a quick stop to check out Exit Glacier. I only ended up hiking to the first viewpoint at the bottom of the Glacier. 

Fast forward 7 years and @go4theglobe and I decided to kick it up a notch. We ended up hiking up into the surrounding mountains to get a better view of the glacier and mountains. We ended up hiking around 7 miles total with about 2,500’ of elevation gain. We were rewarded with some amazing views of the mountains, glaciers and even a curious black bear who was checking us out while he was roaming around the mountain. We made it about as far as we could until the cloud cover became so dense that we couldn’t see the top of the mountain we were on anymore. The wind was starting to pick up so we decided to head back down. On our drive back out to the highway, we stopped at a little restaurant called “Salmon Bake” and had an amazing dinner with some fresh caught Alaskan seafood. All star day, 10/10 would recommend. 

- Kenai Fjords National Park, Alaska

Hey there! I haven’t done one of these before and figured now is as good of time as any to tell y’all a little more about me!

 - Today is my birthday and I’m 33 years old!
 - I am currently on my Honeymoon with @go4theglobe in the Maldives! 
 -  I was born in New Jersey but I grew up in Anchorage, Alaska and have lived in Washington, Montana, Tennessee, and California
 - I love to travel and experience new things. That desire for travel has taken me to 31 countries 
 - I am an only child who was raised by a single mom 
 - My mom passed away in 2019 and that was the hardest thing I have ever been through or dealt with in my life and is something I still struggle with every day
 - I am an athlete who has played just about every sport under the sun. Hockey is by far my favorite sport of all time and I started playing  when I was 4 years old and still play to this day
 - Pole Vaulting is my other passion. I was the Washington State 4A State Champion in the pole vault my senior year of high school, I was a division 1 track and field athlete at the University of Montana where I was a multiple time Big Sky Conference Champion and school record holder in the pole vault #gogriz. After college I competed professionally in the pole vault with the hopes of making the 2016 US Olympic team
 -  I first picked up a camera in 2016 after my pole vaulting career came to an end and I was instantly hooked
 - My favorite things to photograph are landscapes, sports, wildlife and outdoor adventurey stuff
 - I love dogs and get insanely excited every time I see one 
 - My favorite animals are polar bears and it’s a dream of mine to go to the article to photograph them 

That’s is for now but if you made it this far, thank you and I hope you all have a great rest of your day! Cheers 🍻

Little throwback photo from 2019 and the first time I went to the European Christmas markets. I ended up going to markets in 7 different countries and it was such an amazing trip that I still constantly talk about. 

In 2019, my mom had passed away and as the holiday season approached, I didn’t really know what to do for the holiday season. I ended up finding a one way flight to Frankfurt for like $230 so I decided to go for it. I flew out on my birthday with no real plan. I just knew I wanted to get away and check out the Christmas markets. 

Fast forward to today and @go4theglobe and I are on our way to Europe for part 2 of our honeymoon to go to Christmas Markets in France and Belgium! I super stoked to be heading back to Europe and to experience the Christmas Markets her! 

The adventure continues… 

- Tallin, Estonia

Can you find the stingray swimming?
